    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe function `convert_value_to_lua` in `runtime/lua/vim/_options.lua` does not consider escaped commas for arrays.\r\n\r\nThis makes it impossible to use e.g. `vim.opt.errorformat:append` with its default value together with `:make` as the value after appending is invalid. \r\n\r\nThe same goes for maps and sets although my understanding is that they are not currently affected by this as they can't contain commas as values.\r\n\r\nThis issue has previously been mentioned [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/28151).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `:set errorformat=a\\\\,,ab\\\\,,a\\\\,b` (the values `a,`, `ab,` and `a,b`)\r\n2. `:set errorformat`, inspect the result\r\n3. `:lua =vim.opt.errorformat:get()`, notice how even escaped commas split array entries\r\n4. `:lua vim.opt.errorformat:append(\"c\")`\r\n5. `:set errorformat`, notice how (in addition to the appended value) one comma have disappeared since 2., breaking the value\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEscaped commas should not split the array.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n-\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 40\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n-\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n-\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
